The global programmable application-specific integrated circuit (ASIC) market is segmented based on type, application, and geography. In terms of type, the market is categorized into full custom, semi-custom, programmable logic devices (PLD), and field-programmable gate array (FPGA). The full custom segment is expected to witness significant growth due to its customization capabilities tailored to specific requirements of applications. In terms of application, the market is divided into consumer electronics, telecommunication, industrial, automotive, healthcare, and aerospace & defense. The consumer electronics segment is projected to dominate the market owing to the increasing demand for advanced electronic products. Geographically, the market is analyzed across North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, Middle East and Africa, and South America.

